      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/thawab-al-amal:2:20:1",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/20/1",
      "text": [
        ": مَنْ قَالَ سُبْحَانَ اللَّهِ مِنْ غَیْرِ تَعَجُّبٍ خَلَقَ اللَّهُ مِنْهَا طَائِراً لَهُ لِسَانَانِ وَ حَاجِبَانِ یُسَبِّحُ اللَّهَ عَنْهُ فِی الْمُسَبِّحِینَ حَتَّی تَقُومَ السَّاعَهُ وَ مِثْلُ ذَلِکَ الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ وَ لَا إِلَهَ إِلَّا اللَّهُ وَ اللَّهُ أَکْبَرُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. It was narrated to me by Muhammad b. al-Hassan al-Saffar from Muhammad b. Ahmad from his father and al-Hassan b. al-Hussain from Muhammad b. Sinan from Abi al-Jarud from Abi Ja’far (a.s.) who said: “For one who recites Sub-h’aanallaah without surprise Allah will create a bird from it, having a tongue and two wings. It will glorify Allah for that person till the Day of Judgment. The recitation of statement Al-h’amdulillaahi wa laa ilaaha illallaahu wallaahu akbar also holds the same reward.”"
        ]
      }
    },
